# The frontend talks to the API on the SAME origin by default (relative URLs).
# In local dev, Vite proxies /api and /uploads to the backend (see vite.config.js),
# so you normally DON'T need to set anything here.
#
# Only set VITE_API_URL if the API is hosted on a DIFFERENT origin than the app.
# ⚠️ Never set it to http://localhost:4000 for a deployed build — that value gets
# baked into the bundle and the deployed site will try to call your laptop.
# VITE_API_URL=https://api.example.com
